Benjamin Francis Dark (10 November 1793 – 30 May 1836) was an English amateur cricketer who made 6 known appearances in first-class matches from 1814 to 1826.  He was the elder brother of James Dark.
He was mainly associated with Middlesex and Hampshire.

response: James Henry Dark (14 May 1795 – 17 October 1871) was an English professional cricketer who later became a noted patron of the sport and was, from 1835 to 1864, the proprietor of Lord's Cricket Ground. He was the brother of Benjamin Dark.
|Played in 17 matches before going on to own Lord's, which he developed as a ground. Brother of Benjamin Dark.
